reviewText:
I would like to say that this is quite possibly the worst movie ever made, but since I haven't truthfully seen every movie ever made I can't in good conscience make that claim.  That said, if it's not the worst movie ever made I can assure you that it's definitely somewhere in the top 1% of candidates for that title.

I wish I had the 20 minutes of my life back that this movie stole from me before I was able to claw myself back from the murky abyss of disbelief and grief at what a truly awful movie this was and finally turn it off;

The only saving grace was that I was able to watch the little of it that I did for free because it's on Prime, but I almost feel like Amazon should pay damages for the cruel and unusual punishment inflicted on my intelligence by this movie.  This movie made a 3rd grade play look like a roadway production.  If I were one of the main actors in this movie I would have plastic surgery, change my name and move to Thailand out of embarassment.
